Enum ExEnComm.Request

    ExEnComm
    public static enum ExEnComm.Request
extends java.lang.Enum<ExEnComm.Request>
    Requests that ExEn handles: they arrive from outside via network.

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant Description
      Add
      As response to this request an ExEn appends received ICommand(s) to existing ones
      Added
      After successfully processed an Add request, an ExEn broadcasts this command
      Change
      As response to this request an ExEn places the appropriate message into the bus to change Actuator's state.
      A request to change an Actuator's state.
      Changed
      As response to this request an ExEn places the appropriate message into the bus, so rules can react.
      An ExEn is informing a device changed its state (the message is received by a different ExEn from the one that hosts the device).
      Error
      Used by ExEn to report an internal error occurred in ExEn (this is not a real request)
      ErrorAdding
      Used by ExEn to report an internal error occurred in ExEn when adding commands (this is not a real request)
      ErrorDeleting
      Used by ExEn to report an internal error occurred in ExEn when deleting commands (this is not a real request)
      Execute  
      Exit
      As response to this request an ExEn gently finishes itself execution
      List
      As response to this request an ExEn returns a JSON array with all hosted ICommands
      Listed
      After successfully processed a List request, an ExEn broadcasts this command
      Read
      ExEn has to tell the drivers to read their device's value
      Readed
      A driver is informing that a new value was read: it can or can not change a device's state
      Remove
      As response to this request an ExEn deletes one or more existing ICommands
      Removed
      After successfully processed a Remove request, an ExEn broadcasts this command
